HEADWORD: Peccable
<hw>Pec"ca*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>peccable</ets>. See <er>Peccant</er>.]</ety> <def>Liable to sin;
subject to transgress the divine law.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A frail and
<xex>peccable</xex> mortal.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
